narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The lectures are fairly interesting and the videos shown in the class are very poweful. The readings are helpful for writing the short and longer papers. I definitely recommend this course to another student. You would be surprised how interesting this subject is.
I highly recommend Anthropology 182 to anybody of any interest and background. Truly a fulfilling experience.
Take it! This is a great class if you're interested in primate ecology and their social behavior. Nonhuman primates are definitely more diverse than I had originally thought.
Yes, great social science credit for biology majors. Work load is not demanding (no memorization required) but material is valuable.
